Description: "General" voice number unspecified as to location
Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_VOICE
OLI_PHONETYPE_AGENTCSA
Definition: Carrier's phone number agent will use for customer service.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_BUSTOLLFREE
Definition: This is a business toll free number for a Corporation. i.e. 1-800..

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_CLAIMCENTER
Definition: Indicates that the phone number is the phone number for claim inquiries or claim processing information.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_CLIENTCSA
Definition: Carrier's phone number the client will use for customer service.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_FAX
Definition: This value is used when a fax number is given and the party does not indicate whether or not it is their business or personal fax number.If a more specific fax type code is available, it should be used instead of this code. This code should only be used when a fax number is provided and there is no indication as to whether it is a home or business fax.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_HDQRTRS
Definition: The main phone number for a company or organization's headquarters location.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_PREVIOUS
Definition: "Previous" where type (Home, Business, etc.) is unknown or not applicable.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_PRIMARY
Definition: A phone number that has been designated as the primary number for contact by phone.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_ALTERNATE
Definition: A phone number that has been designated as the secondary or alternate number for contact by phone.

Name: OLI_PHONETYPE_SMSTEXT
Definition: Used to designate a phone number that is able to receive SMS text messages.
